HEADWORD: Haiduck
<hw>Hai"duck</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧"d⟦usdot⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>haiduck</ets>, <ets>heiduck</ets>, fr. Hung.
<ets>hajdu</ets>.]</ety> <def>Formerly, a mercenary foot soldier in
Hungary, now, a halberdier of a Hungarian noble, or an attendant in
German or Hungarian courts.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hayduck</asp>, <asp>haiduk</asp>, <asp>heiduc</asp>,
<asp>heyduck</asp>, and <asp>heyduk</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

